<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="525" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,364,826]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
1. Antenna with 11 antennomeres (
<figureCitation box="[538,607,364,386]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[151,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1. Photos of Protoctonus groehni gen. et sp. nov. (female, holotype). A. Habitus, left side. B. Habitus, right side. C. Head and basal antennomeres, front view. D. Antenna. E. Head and mesoscutum, dorsolateral view. F. Metasoma and ovipositor, dorsolateral view. G. Wings. H. Distal part of fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854002/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
)—Flagellomeres starting from fifth moniliform (
<figureCitation box="[1087,1164,364,386]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[151,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1. Photos of Protoctonus groehni gen. et sp. nov. (female, holotype). A. Habitus, left side. B. Habitus, right side. C. Head and basal antennomeres, front view. D. Antenna. E. Head and mesoscutum, dorsolateral view. F. Metasoma and ovipositor, dorsolateral view. G. Wings. H. Distal part of fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854002/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Radial (r, 3-SR, SR1) vein and metacarp (1-R1) almost reaching distal margin of fore wing (
<figureCitation box="[847,927,393,415]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[151,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1. Photos of Protoctonus groehni gen. et sp. nov. (female, holotype). A. Habitus, left side. B. Habitus, right side. C. Head and basal antennomeres, front view. D. Antenna. E. Head and mesoscutum, dorsolateral view. F. Metasoma and ovipositor, dorsolateral view. G. Wings. H. Distal part of fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854002/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">Figs 1G</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[937,970,393,414]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,868,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-758@5.[151,1435,850,1363]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2. Figures of Protoctonus groehni gen. et sp. nov. (female, holotype). A. Fore wing. B. Ovipositor sheaths." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854004" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854004/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">2A</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor sheaths (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1253,393,415]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[151,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1. Photos of Protoctonus groehni gen. et sp. nov. (female, holotype). A. Habitus, left side. B. Habitus, right side. C. Head and basal antennomeres, front view. D. Antenna. E. Head and mesoscutum, dorsolateral view. F. Metasoma and ovipositor, dorsolateral view. G. Wings. H. Distal part of fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854002/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">Figs 1F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1263,1292,393,414]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,868,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-758@5.[151,1435,850,1363]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2. Figures of Protoctonus groehni gen. et sp. nov. (female, holotype). A. Fore wing. B. Ovipositor sheaths." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854004" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854004/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">2B</figureCitation>
) subtriangular, tapered towards apex and curved downwards, entirely covered by dense and short setae; sheath 2.6 × longer than its maximum basal width.......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Davidian &amp; Manukyan &amp; Belokobylskij, 2022" authorityName="Davidian &amp; Manukyan &amp; Belokobylskij" authorityYear="2022" box="[1224,1340,452,473]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Protoctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1224,1340,452,473]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">Protoctonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1436,452,473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,452,473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,364,826]" box="[151,1436,481,503]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,481,503]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
- Antenna with 12 
<emphasis box="[386,398,482,503]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">–</emphasis>
16 antennomeres....................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,364,826]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
2. Petiole of metasoma short and wide, its length almost equal to width at spiracle level. Propodeum without areola and keels. —Antenna with 14–15 antennomeres, moniliform. Ovipositor sheath straight, subtriangular shape, strongly tapered towards apex......................................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Foerster" authorityName="Foerster" authorityYear="1862" box="[1285,1437,598,620]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aclitus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1285,1352,598,619]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">Aclitus</emphasis>
Foerster
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,364,826]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="525">- Petiole of metasoma elongate, its length distinctly larger than width at level of spiracles. Propodeum with delineated medial areola.............................................................................................. 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,364,826]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
3. Ovipositor sheaths curved downwards, gradually tapered towards acuminate apex. Petiole of mesosoma almost parallel-sided behind prominent spiracular tubercles. Antenna with 12–14 antennomeres, evenly thick.......... .. 
<taxonomicName authority="Mackauer" authorityName="Mackauer" authorityYear="1961" box="[1217,1436,716,738]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Calaphidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1334,716,737]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">Calaphidius</emphasis>
Mackauer
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,364,826]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
- Ovipositor sheaths straight or very weakly curved downwards, gradually tapered towards obtuse apex. Petiole of mesosoma distinctly concave behind prominent spiracular tubercles. Antenna with 13–16 antennomeres, slender but weakly thickened apically......................................................................... .... 
<taxonomicName authority="Mackauer" authorityName="Mackauer" authorityYear="1959" box="[1228,1436,804,826]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Falciconus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1228,1335,804,825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">Falciconus</emphasis>
Mackauer
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
